# External Interfaces Architecture

When implementing external interfaces, place them as feature modules under `backend/app/features/` and keep routers thin.

- Use one module per external system under `backend/app/features/interfaces/<interface_key>/`.
- Use typed contracts, client transport, mapper, and service orchestration separation.
- Routers must not call external endpoints directly; call feature services.
- Keep external payload shapes decoupled from SQLAlchemy and internal API schemas.
